## Architecture Rules

### Chrome Extension Component Responsibilities

**Never violate these separations:**

1. **Popup** - UI only, no business logic
   - ❌ Do not access microphone directly
   - ❌ Do not perform audio processing
   - ✅ Only send messages to background
   - ✅ Display data received from background

2. **Background Service Worker** - Orchestration only
   - ❌ Do not access microphone
   - ❌ Do not access DOM
   - ✅ Route messages between components
   - ✅ Manage offscreen document lifecycle

3. **Offscreen Document** - Audio processing only
   - ✅ Access microphone via getUserMedia
   - ✅ Perform audio calculations
   - ✅ Send results to background
   - ❌ Do not manipulate tab DOM

4. **Content Script** - Visual feedback only
   - ✅ Create/manage overlay element
   - ✅ Respond to show/hide messages
   - ❌ Do not access microphone

### Message Flow Pattern

**Always follow:**
```
User Action (Popup)
  → Message to Background
  → Background orchestrates
  → Messages to Offscreen/Content
  → Response back through Background
  → Update Popup UI
```

**Never allow direct communication between:**
- Popup ↔ Offscreen
- Popup ↔ Content Script
- Offscreen ↔ Content Script

**Always go through Background Service Worker as the message router.**

## Common Pitfalls to Avoid

### 1. Async Message Handlers
```typescript
// ❌ WRONG - Missing return true
chrome.runtime.onMessage.addListener((request, sender, sendResponse) => {
  handleAsync().then(sendResponse);
  // Missing return true - response won't be sent!
});

// ✅ CORRECT
chrome.runtime.onMessage.addListener((request, sender, sendResponse) => {
  handleAsync().then(sendResponse);
  return true; // Keeps message channel open
});
```

### 2. Resource Cleanup
```typescript
// ❌ WRONG - Memory leak
stopMonitoring() {
  this.isMonitoring = false;
  // Forgot to close AudioContext!
}

// ✅ CORRECT
stopMonitoring() {
  this.isMonitoring = false;
  if (this.audioContext) {
    this.audioContext.close();
    this.audioContext = null;
  }
  if (this.stream) {
    this.stream.getTracks().forEach(track => track.stop());
  }
}
```

### 3. Documentation Duplication
```
// ❌ WRONG - Duplicating content
Update apps/mobile/README.md with full architecture
Also update docs/tech-spec/mobile.md with same content

// ✅ CORRECT - Single source of truth
Update docs/tech-spec/mobile.md with full architecture
Update apps/mobile/README.md with brief mention + link
```

